1 (2) The following gambling activities may be conducted during a wild west casino night:
2 (a) live gambling authorized under 23-5-311;
3 (b) the use of an apparatus, implement, or device, by whatever name known, specifically designed
4 to be used in conducting an illegal gambling enterprise, including a faro box, faro layout, roulette wheel, roulette
5 table, craps table, or slot machine;
6 (c) the use of antique gambling devices;
7 (d) card games;
8 (E) raffles; and
9 (F) any gambling activity defined in 23-5-112.
10 (3) A living history nonprofit organization that has obtained a permit MAY conduct a WILD WEST
11 casino night in compliance with the following conditions:
12 (a) except as provided in subsection (3)(B), a WILD WEST casino night may not last more than 12
13 consecutive hours; AND
14 (B) a WILD WEST casino night may be split into two separate, 6-consecutive hour sessions that may
15 not be held on the same day but must be held in the same calendar year.
16 (4) The WILD WEST casino night must be managed and operated only by members of the LIVING
17 HISTORY nonprofit organization that was issued the permit. The members may not be compensated for their
18 services.
19 (5) Only merchandise or cash may be awarded as prizes.
20 (6) Proceeds derived from the WILD WEST casino night, after payment of reasonable administrative
21 expenses, may be used only for a civic, charitable, or educational purpose, and administrative expenses may
22 not exceed 50% of the proceeds.
23 (7) If cash prizes are awarded, the prizes for bingo and keno may not exceed the prize AMOUNTS
24 established in 23-5-412. Live card games must be limited to those authorized in 23-5-311, and the prizes may
25 not exceed the prize amount established in 23-5-312.
26
27 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Application for permit. (1) A living history nonprofit organization may
28 apply to the department for a wild west casino night permit on a form prescribed and furnished by the
